---
description: Commit and push Mac changes after major updates; provide Linux pull commands
alwaysApply: true
---

Linux is the permanent host. Mac pushes code + heavy data; Mac clients use the Linux URL in a browser.

After each major update on Mac:

1. Commit relevant changes (exclude `configs/.env`, secrets, `docs/OMEIA_app_code_bundle.md`, `tests/*_last_run.json`).
2. Run `./scripts/deploy/mac_push_to_linux.sh --code-only` (or full push with `--data-only` when syncing OMEIA-database).
3. End responses with Linux commands:

```bash
cd ~/data4TB/digital-notepad
git pull
./scripts/deploy/linux_bootstrap_all.sh --skip-docker   # or full bootstrap after schema changes
./scripts/start_linux.sh
# Browser: http://$(tailscale ip -4):5173
```

First-time data migration from Mac: `./scripts/deploy/mac_push_to_linux.sh` (includes rsync OMEIA-database).

See `docs/LINUX_PRIMARY_DEPLOYMENT.md`.
